{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "The repo also carries a local `webapp-qa` skill that matches this verification path more directly than the Odysseus-specific fallback, so I\u2019m pulling that in for the browser checks. I\u2019ll keep the actual implementation local, then use the...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_24", "text": "The repo also carries a local `webapp-qa` skill that matches this verification path more directly than the Odysseus-specific fallback, so I\u2019m pulling that in for the browser checks. I\u2019ll keep the actual implementation local, then use the repo\u2019s bundled browser container for screenshots and route validation.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 50, "prompt_index": 21, "prompt_name": "20 \u2014 Frontend App Shell and Routing", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T01:12:46-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_25", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 51, "prompt_index": 21, "prompt_name": "20 \u2014 Frontend App Shell and Routing", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T01:12:46-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "---\nname: webapp-qa\ndescription: Use when interacting with a local webapp in this repo, taking screenshots, and verifying behavior both visually and functionally through the docker-compose dev stack and the bundled Puppeteer runner.\n---\n\n# Webapp QA\n\nUse this skill when the task involves running the local app, exercising it in a browser, taking screenshots, or checking that UI behavior and rendered output match expectations.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Start the local stack with `docker compose up -d --build`.\n2. Confirm the app is healthy with `docker compose ps`.\n3. Run browser checks from the `browser` service with `docker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec <spec-path>`.\n4. Review the generated screenshot under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`.\n\n## App URLs\n\n- From the host machine, the app is available at `http://localhost:8566`.\n- From inside the browser container, use `http://frontend:8566`.\n\n## Puppeteer Specs\n\nThe reusable runner lives at `tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs`.\n\nSpecs are JSON files with this shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"url\": \"http://frontend:8566\",\n  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/example.png\",\n  \"viewport\": { \"width\": 1440, \"height\": 960 },\n  \"steps\": [\n    { \"action\": \"waitForSelector\", \"selector\": \"[data-testid='app-card']\" },\n    { \"action\": \"assertText\", \"text\": \"Hello from FastAPI!\" },\n    { \"action\": \"screenshot\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nSupported actions:\n\n- `goto`\n- `waitForSelector`\n- `waitForText`\n- `click`\n- `type`\n- `press`\n- `hover`\n- `assertSelector`\n- `assertText`\n- `assertUrlIncludes`\n- `waitForTimeout`\n- `screenshot`\n\n## Example\n\nUse `tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json` for a basic smoke test plus screenshot:\n\n```bash\ndocker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec ./examples/homepage.spec.json\n```\n\n## Verification Guidance\n\n- For functional checks, prefer explicit `assertText`, `assertSelector`, and URL assertions over informal observation.\n- For visual checks, capture a screenshot after the page reaches the expected stable state.\n- If a page depends on backend data, verify the user-visible result instead of only checking network readiness.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_25", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 52, "prompt_index": 21, "prompt_name": "20 \u2014 Frontend App Shell and Routing", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T01:12:46-07:00"}
